
  Name:  strcpy
  
  #include <string.h>
  char *strcpy(char *str1, const char *str2);
  
  The strcpy( ) function copies the contents of str2 into str1. 
  str2 must be a pointer to a null-terminated string. 
  The strcpy( ) function returns a pointer to str1. If str1 and 
  str2 overlap, the behavior of strcpy( ) is undefined.

  The following code fragment copies hello into string str:
  char str[80];
  strcpy
  (str, ''hello");
  
  Related Function:  memcpy,strchr,strcmp,and strcmp.
